Blog: https://www.techwithkunal.com/blog/getting-started-with-docker
Introduction : 
one application runs at one server problem , solved by VMWARE (Virtual machines) but vm need separate operating systems, dependies poblem,
migration is consuming and many other problem. open source problems like cann't setup easily.
problem solution: Containers (one os with all things) have container engine.
DOCKER is a tool to create, manage, etc. containers.
but in rality containers run on top of virtual machines.

DOCKER RUNTIME: to start and stop things in containers 
- runc
- containerd

Docker ENGINE: used to interact with docker
Docker DAEMON
Docker CLI

Orchestron engines : allow to manage containers ; more advanced version: Kubernetes
DOCKER/CONTAINER IMAGE:  file that contains all instructions to run an application.

DOCKER FILE(instuctions) -----> DOCKER IMAGE(class) -----> CONTAINER(object)

##docker is under(check blog) OPEN CONTAINER INITAITIVES(oci)  
- RUNTINE SPEC
- IMAGE Specifications


